# Plans — canonical location and numbering

> **Split:** **Rules** for agents live here (`.cursor/rules/`). **Plan `PLAN-*.md` files and checklists** live in `docs/plans/` — see `docs/plans/SYNC.md`.

## Where plans live

- **All engineering implementation plans for this repository MUST be created and maintained as Markdown under `docs/plans/`.**
- That directory is the **single source of truth** for plan content, checklists, and status. See also `docs/plans/SYNC.md`.

## Filename convention (canonical)

- **Pattern:** `PLAN-<number>-<short-slug>.md`
  - **`<number>`** — Stable plan id (integer). One number = one plan line of work. Do not reuse the same number for unrelated plans.
  - **`<short-slug>`** — Lowercase words separated by hyphens (topic in English or Spanish, consistent with existing files).
- **Optional prefixes** (after the number is assigned):
  - **`[completed] `** — Plan finished; checklist done; rename file when closing per git-plan workflow.
  - **`[cancelled] `** — Plan abandoned; keep number in filename for history (e.g. superseded approach).
- **Examples:** `PLAN-30-ws-to-sse.md`, `[completed] PLAN-29-hub-next-migration.md`, `[cancelled] PLAN-30-api-railway.md`

## What is not canonical

- **`.cursor/plans/*.plan.md`** (IDE scratch) are **not** the plan of record. **Copy or recreate** into `docs/plans/PLAN-<n>-<slug>.md` and update `docs/plans/README.md` when the work is real.

## New plans

- Choose the **next free `PLAN-<n>`** consistent with existing files and `README.md`, or follow an explicitly assigned number from the team.
- Add a row to **`docs/plans/README.md`** when introducing a new plan that should appear in the index (unless the team uses another index convention for that plan).
